Note that ∞ and −∞ must always have an exclusive parenthesis rather than an inclusive bracket.
This is because ∞ is not a number, and therefore cannot be in our set. ∞ is really just a symbol
that makes things easier to write, like the intervals above.
The interval (a,b) is called an open interval, and the interval [a,b] is called a closed interval.
