The fact that both of these rules work is extremely significant mathematically because it means
that differentiation is linear. You can take an equation, break it up into terms, figure out the
derivative individually and build the answer back up, and nothing odd will happen.
We now need only one more piece of information before we can take the derivatives of any polynomial.
