= −Asin(ωt)
d
d t (ωt) Bring negative sign in front
= −Asin(ωt)ω Evaluate remaining derivative
v(t) = −ωAsin(ωt). Simplify.
The acceleration is then the second time derivative of position, or simply dv/dt.
a(t) =
d v
d t Definition of acceleration in one dimension
=
