= −ωA
d
d t sin(ωt) Bring constant term outside of derivative
= −ωAcos(ωt)
d
d t (ωt) Differentiate outside function (sine)
= −ωAcos(ωt)ω Evaluate remaining derivative
a(t) = −ω
2Acos(ωt). Simplify.
From Newton’s second law, F = ma, where F is the net force and m is the object’s mass.
F = ma Newton’s second law
= m(−ω
