28.2 Infinite Sums
The most basic, and arguably the most difficult, type of evaluation is to use the formal definition of
a Riemann integral.
28.3 Exact Integrals as Limits of Sums
Using the definition of an integral, we can evaluate the limit as n goes to infinity. This technique
requires a fairly high degree of familiarity with summation IDENTITIES30. This technique is often
referred to as evaluation "by definition," and can be used to find definite integrals, as long as the
integrands are fairly simple. We start with definition of the integral:
