0
(t) and y
0 = g
0
(t)
It’s that simple.
This process works for any amount of variables.
40.2 Slope of Parametric Equations
In the above process, x’ has told us only the rate at which x is changing, not the rate for y, and vice
versa. Neither is the slope.
In order to find the slope, we need something of the form d y
d x .
We can discover a way to do this by simple algebraic manipulation:
y
0
