r
2
i
δθ.
As the number of subintervals n is increased, the approximation of the area continues to improve.
In the limit as n → ∞, the sum becomes the Riemann integral.
Generalization
Using Cartesian coordinates, an infinitesimal area element can be calculated as d A = d x d y. The
substitution rule for multiple integrals states that, when using other coordinates, the Jacobian determinant of the coordinate conversion formula has to be considered:
