3
...
which will also converge for | x | < 1. When x = -1 this is the harmonic series, which diverges’; when
x= 1 this is an alternating series with diminishing terms, which convergesto ln 2 - this is testing the
extremities.
It also lets us write power series for integrals we cannot do exactly such as the error function:
