y
x
Because tan-1 is multivalued, care must be taken to select the right value.
Just as for Cartesian coordinates the unit vectors that point in the x and y directions are special, so
in polar coordinates the unit vectors that point in the r and θ directions are also special.
We will call these vectors rˆ and θˆ , pronounced r-hat and theta-hat. Putting a circumflex over a vector
this way is often used to mean the unit vector in that direction.
Again, on looking at the diagram we see,
i = rˆ cosθ −θˆ sinθ rˆ =
