Curves and parameterizations
Angle between curves
Figure 75
We can then formulate the concept of the angle between two curves by considering the angle between the two tangent vectors. If two curves, parametrized by f1 and f2 intersect at some point,
which means that
f1(s)=f2(t)=c,
the angle between these two curves at c is the angle between the tangent vectors f1&prime;(s) and
