which achieved after pulling f’(p) inside and putting it over a common denominator.
We can’t divide by vectors, so this definition can’t be immediately extended to the multiple variable
case. Nonetheless, we don’t have to: the thing we took interest in was the quotient of two small
distances (magnitudes), not their other properties (like sign). It’s worth noting that ’other’ property
of vector neglected is its direction. Now we can divide by the absolute value of a vector, so lets
rewrite this definition in terms of absolute values
limx→p
