Curl u tells us if the vector u is rotating round a point. The direction of curl u is the axis of rotation.
We can treat vectors in two dimensions as a special case of three dimensions, with uz=0 and Dzu=0.
We can then extend the definition of curl u to two-dimensional vectors
curl u = Dyux −Dxuy
This two dimensional curl is a scalar. In four, or more, dimensions there is no vector equivalent to
the curl.
Example:
